        <h3>Where disease first shows itself</h3>
        <p>The manifestation of a disease may initially be detected at the body level (e.g. fever), at the organ level (e.g. liver, renal, or other organ function tests), or at the tissue level (e.g. degeneration or inflammation). A medical test used to identify a disease process involves a series of procedures — both invasive and non-invasive — performed to determine and screen for the causative factors, in order to reach a treatment modality.</p>
